es were executed for heresy on November 8 and 9. The outrage from the executions led to the Swedish removal of support of the Kalmar Union.","url":"https://www.britannica.com/event/Stockholm-Bloodbath","urlTitle":"Britannica - Stockholm Bloodbath","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702080,"age":23,"year":"1523","julianDay":2277324,"title":"Swedish War of Liberation","description":"The Swedish War of Liberation was a civil war led by nobleman Gustav Vasa. As Christian II heard of the rebellion, he confronted Vasa's men, who won the battle at Brunbacks Ferry. Christian II was defeated by the Swedes in Stockholm and a truce was agreed upon. Vasa was given as a hostage as a show of good faith until the treaty was signed. The Danish King did not keep his word and Vasa was held as a prisoner for two years until his escape. A bounty was placed on Vasa's head. Vasa worked to inspire many to join his cause and lived under disguise until the Danes surrendered in 1525.","url":"https://www.sweden.org.za/swedish-monarchy-gustav-vasa.html","urlTitle":"Sweden.org - Swedish Monarchy Gustav Vasa","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702085,"age":40,"year":"1540","julianDay":2283533,"title":"First Full Swedish Translation of the Bible","description":"The first full Swedish translation of the Bible, known as the Gustav Bible, was completed by Olaus Petri and Laurentius Andreae and published in 1540.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702086,"age":44,"year":"1544","julianDay":2284994,"title":"Sweden Becomes Lutheran Nation","description":"Sweden officially declared itself a Lutheran nation in 1544.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1357053,"age":51,"year":"1551","julianDay":2287551,"description":"Sweden seized territory of Estonia.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Gölin Esbjörnsdotter was born about 1500, in Grangärde, Kopparberg, Sweden, her father, Esbiörn Mårtensson, was 23 and her mother, Martha, was 20. She died in 1560, in her hometown, at the age of 61."},"et":{"about 1500–1560":"umbes 